==English==
===Pronunciation===
*SAMPA: /"naU@%deIz/
===Adverb===

#{{time}}: In these days; at the present time.
#: ''Work that was once done by hands is often done by machine nowadays.''

===Quotations=== <!-- More exact dates, etc.? Neither seems to have found its way onto the web outside online dictionaries -->
*'''Late 1300's:''' — Geoffrey Chaucer : ''Wit that men have now a days''
*'''1594''' — [[Shakespeare]], ''[[s:A_Midsummer_Night's_Dream|A Midsummer Night's Dream]] v 5''
*:and yet, to say the truth, reason and love keep little company together '''now-a-days'''.
*'''Late 1700's:''' — David Garrick : ''What men of spirit, nowadays, Come to give sober judgment of new plays?''

